    <article>
        <h2>Web Essentials 2012</h2>

        <h3>3.2 - October 5, 2013</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Fixed Markdown editor issue</li>
            <li>Improved the LESS validator</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.1 - September 28, 2013 <a href="/nightly/webessentials2012-3.1.vsix">Download</a></h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Re-added TypeScript drag 'n drop</li>
            <li>Re-added TypeScript #regions</li>
            <li>Added Robots.txt Intellisense</li>
            <li>Updated Markdown editor</li>
            <li>Added HTML #region support</li>
            <li>Made fonts and colors for Markdown customizable</li>
            <li>Various bug fixes</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.0 - August 24, 2013 <a href="/nightly/webessentials2012-3.0.vsix">Download</a></h3>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Removed all TypeScript support
                <ul>
                    <li>As agreed with the TypeScript team</li>
                    <li>It's a good thing. <a href="http://madskristensen.net/post/Web-Essentials-2013-Where-is-the-TypeScript-support.aspx">Here's why</a></li>
                    <li><a href="http://blogs.msdn.com/b/typescript/archive/2013/01/21/announcing-typescript-0-8-2.aspx">Compile on save</a> is supported</li>
                    <li><a href="http://typescript.codeplex.com/wikipage?title=Compile-on-Save">Enable Typscript compilation in your project</a></li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Added support for pre-gzipping .js and .css</li>
            <li>Output window no longer hijacked on build</li>
            <li>Robots.txt syntax highlighter</li>
        </ul>

